d to be practical tools for guiding learners' processes of learning and writing a scholarly paper or article and avoiding plagiarism. The implication for teachers and program administrators is a systematic approach for developing self-regulation (control) in EFL/ESL writing. The first part of the book reports on the mixed methods (quantitative and qualitative) research. The second part gives an in-depth report of the 6 cases used in the research. The third part presents tools for systematically developing self-regulation in scholarly (and academic) writing with (a) student and teacher checklists for formative assessment that are valid and reliable; and (b) a model syllabus for teachers that can be adapted across disciplines and genres. These tools deal with learning strategies and their applications to writing and writing instruction.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aAcademic writingxStudy and teaching (Higher)xForeign speakers. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching (Higher)xForeign speakers. 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teaching (Higher) 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teaching (Higher). 4aSecond Language Acquisition, Language Teaching, Foreign Language Education, Applied Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015008550 cprintz978161451378040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451269140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614512691423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781614512691.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus 